text=(:if [ authgroup @tas || authgroup @admins || equal {$Author} '' ]:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=edit|Edit this page]] \\%0aStatus: {GradebookArticles.{$Name}$:Status} %0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!{$:Category}]]%0a%0a!Ainu%0a%0a:Author: justin123%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aA summary of the Ainu People and the Ainu Languages%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aI chose Ainu due to its unique location relative to other native languages in the Asian island of Hokkaido, presently part of Japan. The history of its people and their contact with the Japanese have always been interesting to me and I wanted to investigate more of the language.%0a%0aThe Ainu historically resided in the island of Hokkaido, as well as the northern tip of Honshu, both being large islands comprising of the present day nation of Japan. Additionally, they have settled along Sakhalin Island and the Kuril Islands, now under Russian jurisdiction, the latter of the two being contested by Japan. (1) The IPA transcription of the name is /ˈaɪnuː. The meaning of the word within the Ainu languages is "human". Ainumosir refers to the "land of the Ainu", and Ainu people also refer to themselves as "utari" meaning person. (2)%0a%0aMany decrees by the Japanese government impeded on the Ainu people's land and freedoms, https://www.ainu-assn.or.jp/english/history.html gives a historical list of crimes committed and eventually recognition within the last few decades. %0a%0aThe Ainu languages are critically endangered, with only the mainland dialect of Hokkaido Ainu not having become extinct, and as of 2018 the Japanese government recorded only ~5 native speakers. (3) There are Ainu language resources, especially in Japanese, as well as revitalization efforts from government entities as well as Ainu organizations. https://unilang.org/course.php?res=58 here is a introductory course translated into English. There is a strong enough foundation that heritage centers are able to preserve the language in their works and descriptions and place-names as seen in the Lake Akan Ainu Kotan, a settlement and center for Ainu culture.%0a%0aThere is, historically, much written and said about the Ainu by the Japanese government/institutions that is not representative of them. Many stereotypes were made about the people, as well as the pushing of the myth of a mono-ethnic Japan which has existed to this day, and only recently has the Ainu language and culture been not only accepted by the Japanese people at large but also appreciated. (4) Films and anime incorporating Ainu language and culture have become popular whereas in the past such a thing would be unthinkable.%0a%0a%0aReferences: 1: https://www.ainu-assn.or.jp/english/begin.html 2: https://www.akanainu.jp/en/culture-people 3: https://www.e-stat.go.jp/stat-search/files?page=1&layout=datalist&toukei=00250012&tstat=000001018034&cycle=1&year=20180&month=24101212&tclass1=000001060399&tclass2val=0 4: https://apjjf.org/-Chisato-Kitty-Dubreuil/2589/article.html%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:elseif [ equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:andrewid} '' || equal {Profiles.{$Author}$:section} '' ] :)%0a%0aYou must enter your andrew ID and section before submitting an expansion. %0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a%0a----%0a(:if equal {$Author} {$:Author}:)%0a!!Change article category%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#changearticlecategory:)%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a%0a(:Section: B:)%0a(:Category: IndigenousLanguagesOfTheAmericas:)%0a(:Title: Ainu:)
